parameters:
\nc<>Yeah, you're right. The promised time has long passed. If I
were in the opposite position, I would have lost patience.

\nc<>This is ridiculous. What am I getting hurt for? The one who
should be truly hurt is Reina, not me.

\nc<>...If things were going to turn out like this, I shouldn't
have become a magical girl--
\nc<>...Huh? Why are you looking so surprised?
\nc<>I just walked here normally from over there, you know?

\nc<>No, not that! I, I stood you up on our promise. So why, why
are you still...
\nc<>...? I see! So that's what you were worried about?

\nc<>By the way, did you already forget? Why did I get close to
you, Senpai?
\nc<>B-Because I wanted to become your sidekick...?

\nc<>Yes, that's right! I admired my senpai, who is a magical
girl, and I wanted to become a source of strength for them.

\nc<>I wouldn't want a senpai who doesn't seem like a hero,
right?

\nc<>It's okay to stand me up on our promise. We can always go
play together again, no matter how many times.

\nc<>It's okay if you don't prioritize me. I don't want that
either.

\nc<>So, it would be great if you could continue to be yourself,
Senpai.

\nc<>(What should I do? It's really embarrassing, or rather, I
can't make eye contact...)

\nc<>S-So, by the way, what's the important thing you wanted to
talk about? It's a bit late, but if there's anything I can
help with, please let me know.
\nc<>Ah... well, let's see. I'll talk about it a little later.
\nc<>For now, I've found what I wanted.
\nc<>I obtained the memory R2: A Choice Without Regret.
